think%20it's%20gonna%20move%20the%20needle%20in%20any%20direction.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMusk%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrump%20has%20continued%20to%20pressure%20Republicans%20to%20support%20the%20bill%2C%20and%20the%20White%20House%20has%20said%20that%20those%20who%20vote%20against%20it%20should%20face%20primary%20challenges.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrump%20himself%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdonald-trump-elon-musk-budget-bill-response-attack-explained-why-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Enot%20yet%20responded%20to%20Musk%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20though%20Johnson%20told%20reporters%20that%20the%20president%20is%20%26quot%3Bnot%20delighted%20that%20Elon%20did%20a%20180%26quot%3B%20on%20the%20bill.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMusk's%20broadside%20against%20the%20bill%2C%20according%20to%20him%2C%20is%20about%20its%20impact%20on%20the%20debt.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMultiple%20forecasters%20who%20have%20analyzed%20the%20bill%2C%20including%20the%20Congressional%20Budget%20Office%20and%20the%20Committee%20for%20a%20Responsible%20Federal%20Budget%2C%20have%20estimated%20that%20the%20current%20version%20of%20the%20bill%20would%20add%20more%20than%20%242%20trillion%20to%20the%20deficit%20over%20the%20next%2010%20years.%20Musk%20has%20argued%20that%20this%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-criticizes-trump-spending-bill-deficit-undermines-doge-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eundermines%20DOGE%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20has%20been%20trying%20to%20significantly%20reduce%20federal%20spending.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERepublicans%20were%20already%20arguing%20about%20this%20amongst%20themselves.%20Fiscal%20conservatives%20like%20Sen.%20Rand%20Paul%20of%20Kentucky%20and%20Sen.%20Ron%20Johnson%20of%20Wisconsin%20say%20that%20the%20version%20of%20the%20bill%20that%20passed%20the%20House%20last%20month%20adds%20too%20much%20to%20the%20debt%2C%20and%20they're%20now%20seeking%20to%20amend%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMost%20Republicans%2C%20however%2C%20have%20argued%20that%20outside%20projections%20about%20the%20bill's%20impact%20on%20the%20debt%20are%20flawed%20and%20don't%20account%20for%20potential%20economic%20growth%20as%20a%20result%20of%20the%20bill's%20eventual%20passage.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20those%20who%20agree%20with%20Musk%20don't%20seem%20to%20believe%20that%20his%20comments%20will%20strengthen%20their%20hand%20that%20much.%20%26quot%3BSure%2C%20it%20helps%20bolster%20the%20case%2C%26quot%3B%20Sen.%20Ron%20Johnson%20told%20reporters%20of%20Musk's%20tweet.%20%26quot%3BBut%20again%2C%20the%20President%20wants%20to%20balance%20the%20budget%20as%20well.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPerhaps%20the%20biggest%20reason%20why%20Musk's%20comments%20are%20unlikely%20to%20tank%20the%20bill%3A%20It's%20the%20centerpiece%20of%20Trump's%20legislative%20agenda%2C%20and%20it's%20simply%20too%20important%20to%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20bill%20includes%20a%20permanent%20extension%20of%20tax%20cuts%20that%20Trump%20and%20Republicans%20first%20enacted%20in%202017%2C%20contains%20new%20funding%20for%20border%20security%20and%20immigration%20enforcement%2C%20and%20is%20chock%20full%20of%20other%20GOP%20priorities%20that%20they're%20not%20going%20to%20give%20up%20simply%20because%20of%20Musk's%20concern%20about%20the%20deficit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAll%20the%20things%20that%20are%20in%20this%20bill%20are%20so%20important%20for%20the%20US%20economy%2C%20it's%20going%20to%20be%20jet%20fuel%20for%20the%20US%20economy%2C%26quot%3B%20Speaker%20Johnson%20told%20reporters%20on%20Wednesday.%20%26quot%3BThe%20risk%20of%20not%20getting%20it%20done%20is%20enormous%2C%20not%20just%20for%20the%20Republican%20Party%2C%20but%20for%20the%20country.%20We've%20got%20to%20do%20this.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20government%20funding%20bill%20that%20Musk%20helped%20tank%20in%20December%2C%20on%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20was%20a%20bipartisan%20piece%20of%20legislation%20that%20